pullRequest.body:
This branch is just for benching.

Compare to #7849, which benches nightly testing. The changes from that branch's bench to this branch's bench are [here](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/e7b27246-a3e6-496a-b552-ff4b45c7236e/to/e7b27246-a3e6-496a-b552-ff4b45c7236e?hash1=62bbf6d19813dde7b2487a48393c8831e64dacfd&hash2=32f7c7c8847731c65a954f25f0f82c84c81c1d61).

There are no significant changes.

To find these on speedcenter manually, search "2712" and compare the branch `bench-nightly-testing-for-2712` to `lean-pr-testing-2712`.

nodes.body:
Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/3eea3986-e7ba-49d9-b221-f9130d18e49c) for commit 32f7c7c8847731c65a954f25f0f82c84c81c1d61.
There were [significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/c547b597-3f6b-45f5-b436-57839d2058b5/to/3eea3986-e7ba-49d9-b221-f9130d18e49c) against commit 3ce43c18f614b76e161f911b75a3e1ef641620ff:
```diff
  Benchmark                                                  Metric         Change
  ================================================================================
- ~Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.AffineScheme                    instructions     2.9%
+ ~Mathlib.Analysis.Analytic.Basic                           instructions   -17.1%
+ ~Mathlib.Analysis.Analytic.Composition                     instructions   -57.7%
+ ~Mathlib.Analysis.Analytic.Inverse                         instructions   -12.7%
- ~Mathlib.RepresentationTheory.GroupCohomology.Resolution   instructions     5.6%
```
I am closing this PR since it seems it has fulfilled its purpose. Feel free to reopen it.
